      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The MACRS (Modified Accelerated Cost Recovery System) formula for a heavy equipment like an industrial excavator is a bit complex, but I'll break it down for you. The MACRS formula is a tax deduction system used to depreciate long-term assets. For a 2023 purchase, the asset would fall under Class 7, which has a 15-year recovery period.\n\nThe MACRS formula involves calculating the asset's cost, adjusted for the recovery period, and then applying the depreciation rates. The rates for Class 7 are 14.29%, 17.46%, 19.29%, 23.3%, 27.46%, 31.46%, and 33.33% for years 1 through 7, respectively.\n\nTo calculate the depreciation, you'll need to know the asset's cost, adjusted for any sales tax or other expenses. The formula is:\n\nDepreciation = (Cost - Adjusted Cost) x Depreciation Rate\n\nFor example, if the asset's cost is $500,000 and the adjusted cost is $450,000, the depreciation for the first year would be:\n\nDepreciation = ($500,000 - $450,000) x 14.29",
